  "requirements": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "text": "Define \"law.\" Tell some of its sources. Describe the functions it serves.",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13494",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "text": "Discuss TWO of the following:",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13477",
      "requirements": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "Justinian's Code, the Code of Hammurabi, and the Magna Carta",
          "internal_parent_id": "13477",
          "internal_id": "13478",
          "requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "The development of the jury system",
          "internal_parent_id": "13477",
          "internal_id": "13479",
          "requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "text": "Two famous trials in history.",
          "internal_parent_id": "13477",
          "internal_id": "13480",
          "requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "text": "Tell what civil law is; tell what criminal law is. Tell the main  differences between them. Give examples of each.",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13496",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "text": "Ask five people (not more than one from your immediate  family) about the role of law enforcement officers in our society. Discuss their answers with them. Go to a law enforcement  officer in your neighborhood and ask about his or her responsibilities and duties. Report your findings to your counselor.",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13497",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "5",
      "text": "Discuss with your counselor several laws that were passed to protect the consumer and the seller. Describe several organizations that provide help to consumers and sellers.",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13498",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "6",
      "text": "Do ONE of the following:",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13481",
      "requirements": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "text": "Attend a session of a civil or criminal court. Write 250 words or more on what you saw.",
          "internal_parent_id": "13481",
          "internal_id": "13482",
          "requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "text": "Plan and conduct a mock trial with your troop or school class. After the trial is over, discuss it with the group.",
          "internal_parent_id": "13481",
          "internal_id": "13483",
          "requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "7",
      "text": "Arrange a visit with a lawyer who works for a business, bank, title company, or government agency. Find out his or her duties and responsibilities. Report what you have learned.",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13499",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "8",
      "text": "Explain the requirements for becoming a lawyer in your state. Describe how judges are selected in your state.",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13500",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "9",
      "text": "Make a list of 15 jobs that deal with some aspects of law or legal processes. Tell which you prefer. Why?",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13501",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "10",
      "text": "Tell where people can go to obtain the help of a lawyer if they are unable to pay for one. Tell what you can do if you can afford a lawyer but do not know of any in your area.",
      "internal_parent_id": null,
      "internal_id": "13495",
      "requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "11",
